  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The intended use scope is VAD implant support for end-stage heart failure patients; the quantity of interest is the Normalized Index of Hemolysis under steady-state operating conditions at 2500–4500 RPM and 3–6 L/min flow. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment completed under Minimal profile conformance.",
